<p><strong>OpenGL</strong> and <strong>DirectX</strong> are two different graphics rendering methods. Both versions of <strong>Jujutsu Kaisen Mugen</strong> contain the same characters and content. If you are unsure which one to pick, go with <strong>DirectX</strong> — it works on most Windows PCs. If you experience graphical glitches, try the <strong>OpenGL</strong> version instead.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">Can I play JJK Mugen on my Android phone?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p>Yes! Although there is no native Android APK, you can use <strong>Winlator</strong> (recommended) or <strong>Exagear</strong> to emulate the Windows version on your <strong>Android mobile</strong>. We recommend downloading a lighter version like <strong>V4, V5 or V6</strong> for the best mobile experience. Check the full step-by-step guides above.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">How many characters does JJK Mugen V9 have?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p><strong>Jujutsu Kaisen Mugen V9</strong> features <strong>78 playable characters</strong>, including multiple versions of popular fighters like Gojo (6 versions), Sukuna (11 versions), Itadori (5 versions), and Yuta (3 versions). The roster covers all major story arcs from <strong>Shibuya</strong> to <strong>Shinjuku</strong>.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">Which version should I download for Android mobile?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p>For <strong>Android emulation</strong> through Winlator or Exagear, we recommend <strong>JJK Mugen V4, V5 or V6</strong>. These versions weigh under 2 GB extracted, which makes them much easier to run on mobile hardware. The latest V9 (5.85 GB) may struggle on phones with less than 8 GB RAM.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">What are the keyboard controls for Jujutsu Kaisen Mugen?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p><strong>Keyboard:</strong> Arrow Keys for movement — A/S/D for Light/Medium/Heavy Attack — Q/W/E for Special Moves — Space to Jump.</p>
<p><strong>Controller:</strong> D-Pad/Stick for movement — X/Y/B for Attack Buttons — LB/RB for Special Moves — A to Jump.</p>
<p>You can customize all controls in the <strong>M.U.G.E.N options menu</strong> before starting a match.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">Is Winlator or Exagear better for playing JJK Mugen on Android?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p><strong>Winlator</strong> is the recommended option for modern phones — it is actively maintained, free, open-source, and offers better compatibility with newer MUGEN games. <strong>Exagear</strong> is a good alternative for <strong>older or lower-end devices</strong> since it uses fewer resources, but it is no longer officially updated.</p>
</div>
</details>

<details class="su-spoiler">
<summary class="su-spoiler-title">Will there be a Jujutsu Kaisen Mugen V10?</summary>
<div class="su-spoiler-content">
<p>The game is created and maintained by <strong>Dark Night</strong>, who has been consistently releasing new versions. Since V9 was released in February 2026, it is likely that <strong>V10 will arrive later in 2026</strong>. When it does, we will update this page with the new download links.</p>
